data.title: Synopsis of Philippine History Pre-Spanish Times
data.meta_description:
PHILIPPINE HISTORY - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. 1. The document summarizes Philippine history from pre-Spanish times through Spanish colonial rule, the American era, Japanese occupation, independence and the modern era. It covers major events, leaders and the transfer of power from Spain to the US to Japan and finally to an independent Philippines. 
2. Key events included the arrival of Ferdinand Magellan in 1521, Spain's rule for over 300 years, the declaration of independence in 1898 and subsequent Philippine-American War, Japanese occupation during WWII, and the postwar periods including Martial Law and the People Power Revolution. 
3. The summary highlights the major political transitions and periods in Philippine history.
